word_mean_info__list.difference: 普通用词，指步行的速度，常引申指活动的进度或生产率。
作“速度”讲时，与speed同义，可换用。作速率解时，指相对增长的速度，也指两种相比较而得出的标准速度。
普通用词，指单位时间内行进的固定速度或速率，也指可能达到的最高速度。
技术用词，指物体沿着一定方向运动时的速率。
与appraise相似，指使判断绝对准确，但多用于对人物的某方面的评价，很少用于评价某物的市场价值。
专指评定价值等级的高低。
侧重指一般人对某物的价值或价格所作的估计。
原义指对为确定交多少税而估计，引申指通过估价以便更好利用。
通常指由个人作出的主观估价。
指以专家身份作了最终精确的估价。

list.abstract: Rate（英[reɪt]，美[reɪt]），英文单词。作名词为比率；价格。作动词为评估；对… 估价。短语搭配有birth rate（出生率）。例句为“Its annual rate of poverty alleviation.（它的年减贫率。）” Rate的名词近义词有degree；及物动词近义词有assess；不及物动词近义词有hop on。

yingyinNormal.en: Joey? Yeah? Chappy's heart rate has slowed way down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，怎么了Chppy的心脏越跳越慢了。

yingyinNormal.en: The unemployment rate for those with a bachelor's degree is less than one-third of the rate for those without a high school diploma.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拥有本科学历人员的失业率比没有高中学历的人要低三分之一。

yingyinNormal.en: On a scale of one to ten, how would you rate your pain? Zero.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从一到十，你的痛感是几级? 零。

yingyinNormal.en: Nice big smile, Harry. Together, you and I rate the front page.
yingyinNormal.zh: 笑容大一点，哈利。我们的合照将会登上头版。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets》

yingyinNormal.en: All right. How does the flow rate in a pipe depend on its diameter?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，管直径如何决定流量。

yingyinNormal.en: Ambassador, this rate is unwarranted. We will find a suitable figure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大使他说的数量实在太无理了，我们会协商出一个合适的数量。

yingyinNormal.en: What's the exchange rate? None of your business. Take it or leave it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 汇率是多少？不关你事。成还不成？

yingyinNormal.en: Time is catching up with us. At this rate, we are headed for catastrophe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 时间已经十分紧迫，照这样下去，我们会大难临头。

yingyinNormal.en: For the first time in six years, the unemployment rate is below 6 percent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 六年以来的第一次失业率降低到6%以下。

yingyinNormal.en: Like us, they appear to have a population growth rate that's unsustainable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 向我们一样，他们也有过度的人口增长。

yingyinNormal.en: What's most alarming is the rate at which their military power is expanding.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最令人警惕的是他们的军事扩展速度。

yingyinNormal.en: On a scale of 1 to 10, how would you rate your pain? Physical, or emotional?
yingyinNormal.zh: 从一到十级，你的疼痛指数是？你是说生理上的，还是心理上的？

yingyinNormal.en: Cuttlefish genes were added to help her withstand an accelerated growth rate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她的体内加入了乌贼基因，帮助减缓快速的生长率。

yingyinNormal.en: We've reduced the unemployment rate from 10% in October of 2009 to 6.1% today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们将失业率从2009年10月的10%降低到今天的6.1%。

yingyinNormal.en: Similar to 1950s, London and LA, it's painful with higher growth rate, you see?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过，这不比20世纪50年代那时的伦敦和洛杉矶好多了吗？是的，高速的经济增长总是伴随着痛苦。

yingyinNormal.en: After it passes the blood-brain barrier, your heart rate would shoot up to 160.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在突破了血脑屏障之后，心率会爆涨到160。

yingyinNormal.en: Every country in the world dreams of having the growth rate of Shanghai and China.
yingyinNormal.zh: 世界上每座城市都梦想着有上海和中国的发展速度。

yingyinNormal.en: ...have you ever refused to rate...Ma'am, that's delusional. We stand behind them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是否有曾拒绝过。这是痴人说梦，我们相信这些公司。

yingyinNormal.en: And if the magnetic pulse rate goes up before the quakes, then we're predicting them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果在地震前磁脉冲率上升的话，那么我们可以提前预测。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi, everybody. For the first time in more than 6 years the unemployment rate is below 6%.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家好。6年多以来的第一次失业率降到了6%以下。

examination_example.sentence: In February, at 3.5 per cent and 5.5 per cent respectively, unemployment <highlight>rates</highlight> in Canada and the United States were at generational lows.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2月份，加拿大和美国的失业率分别为3.5%和5.5%，处于世代以来的最低水平。

examination_example.sentence: Some AI software can analyze and optimize marketing email subject lines to increase open <highlight>rates</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些人工智能软件可以分析和优化营销电子邮件主题，以提高点击率。

examination_example.sentence: Their grades are lower and their dropout <highlight>rates</highlight> are higher.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的成绩更低，辍学率更高。

sense_info_list.en: assign a standard or value to something according to a particular scale

examination_example.sentence: They asked participants to watch silent 10-second video clips of professors and to <highlight>rate</highlight> the instructor's overall effectiveness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们要求参与者观看教授的10秒无声视频片段，并对导师的整体效率进行评价。

examination_example.sentence: A Harvard Business School study found that observers consistently <highlight>rated</highlight> those who were upfront about themselves more highly, while those who hid lost trustworthiness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 哈佛商学院的一项研究发现，观察人士对那些坦率的人的评价总是更高，而那些隐瞒真相的人则失去了可信度。

examination_example.sentence: Britons <highlight>rate</highlight> "the countryside" alongside the royal family, Shakespeare and the National Health Service (NHS) as what makes them proudest of their country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国人将“乡村”与王室、莎士比亚和国民医疗服务体系（NHS）相提并论，认为这是他们为自己的国家感到最自豪的地方。

examination_example.sentence: Then they <highlight>rated</highlight> the degree which they had used intuition ("gut feelings," "hunches," "my heart").
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后，他们对自己使用直觉(“直觉”、“预感”、“自己的心”)的程度进行评级。

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>rated</highlight> each child's overall sympathy level and his or her tendency to feel negative emotions after moral transgressions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她对每个孩子的总体同情水平以及他们在道德越界后感受到负面情绪的倾向进行了评级。

examination_example.sentence: The interviewers had <highlight>rated</highlight> applicants on a scale of one to five.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 面试官对应聘者用1到5分的分数进行评级。

examination_example.sentence: adopting a new <highlight>rate</highlight>-increase mechanism.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 采用新的提高利率的机制。

examination_example.sentence: Most of the money would come from a penny-per-letter permanent <highlight>rate</highlight> increase and from shifting postal retirees into Medicare.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大部分资金将来自每封信一便士的永久税率的提高，以及将邮政退休人员转移到医疗保险中。

word_usage.usage:
表示“速度”
speed指交通工具等运动的速率或事情发生的速度。
pace指人步行的速度，常引申为生活、变化等的速度。
rate常指某事在一段时间内发生的速度，可与 speed 换用。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: “率”，指价值、花费、速度等与其他数量单位相比较，通常指一个比值数。
则指表明一个量包含另一个量倍数大小的数字，通常指一种比例。

examination_example.sentence: As expected, there was a much higher <highlight>rate</highlight> of attrition (减员) among scientists who didn't get grants.

examination_example.sentence: Too much workout often slows metabolic <highlight>rates</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: They had slow metabolic <highlight>rates</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的代谢率很低。

examination_example.sentence: Data collected from the device could be used to recognize different participants based on how they typed, with very low error <highlight>rates</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从该设备收集的数据可以根据不同的参与者的打字方式来识别他们，错误率非常低。

examination_example.sentence: And they tended to lose cognitive (认知) function at a much slower <highlight>rate</highlight> than those with the least mentally challenging jobs.

examination_example.sentence: Hospital patients who see tree branches out their window are likely to recover at a faster <highlight>rate</highlight> than patients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 看到窗外树枝的医院病人很可能比病人恢复得更快。

examination_example.sentence: I can certainly change that for you, but there will be a change in the room <highlight>rate</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我当然可以为您更改，但是房费会有所变化。

examination_example.sentence: The new <highlight>rate</highlight> is $199 per night, instead of the original $179.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新的房价是每晚199美元，而不是原来的179美元。

examination_example.sentence: Movie reviewers would not <highlight>rate</highlight> it highly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 影评人不会给它很高的评价。

examination_example.sentence: It's one of the best-<highlight>rated</highlight> hostels in the city, and for good reason.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是城里评级最好的旅馆之一，理由很充分。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2018-2021年全国重点省市中考试卷，包括听力、阅读、完形、单选、填空、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。
